<subSubSection id="C3266529FFBBFFAEFF0CFE23D895FD91" pageId="5" pageNumber="330" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8336A2FFBBFFAEFF0CFE23D895FD91" blockId="5.[151,1437,361,784]" pageId="5" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis id="B948EAB0FFBBFFAEFF0CFE23D97BFE22" bold="true" box="[199,314,397,423]" pageId="5" pageNumber="330">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(transcribed). Length 
<quantity id="4CC49B47FFBBFFAEFDF3FE20DAD3FE2D" box="[568,658,398,425]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="330" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. Frons impressed between eyes; scapus triangular with a long tuft of setae; club broad with two weakly procurved sutures. Elytral striae not impressed, interstriae with rows of erect fine setae; declivity steep, apex mucronate. Legs widen apically, with three or four small denticles at the outer apical edge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
